title: Week 5 honor roll: Ribault duo, St. Augustine linebacker lead the way
text:
Week 5 honor roll: Ribault duo, St. Augustine linebacker lead the way 
By Justin Barney Thu, Oct 1, 2015 @ 8:15 pm Photos Gary McCullough/For the St. Augustine Record St. Augustine linebacker Connor Evans, shown in this 2014 photo, had a huge defensive game in the Yellow Jackets 24-17 win over Bartram Trail in OT on Sept. 25. 
A look at area players who posted stellar performances during Week 5 of the high school football season. 

HONOR ROLL 
Keylan Brown, RB, Oakleaf: Rushed for 193 yards and three TDs as the Knights beat Clay, 48-20. 
Davion Dubose, RB, West Nassau: Rushed for 205 yards and three TDs in a 26-14 win over Yulee. 
Connor Evans, LB, Jahquise Russell, RB, St. Augustine: Evans had 16 tackles, an INT and broke up a pass in a 24-14 OT win over Bartram Trail. Russell rushed for 188 yards on 28 carries and caught the winning TD in OT. 
Detronce Limbrick, QB/DB, WRs Karon Ashley, Malik Ferrell, Potterâ€™s House: Limbrick was 20 of 32 for 354 yards and four TDs passing, and added six tackles and an interception on defense in a 42-0 win over Mayo Lafayette. Ashley (six catches, 146 yards, three TDs) and Ferrell (eight catches, 123 yards, TD) also starred. 
DeSean McNair, RB, Terry Stripling, DB, Ribault: McNair had 178 rushing yards on 35 carries, and Stripling intercepted a pair of passes and returned one 50 yards for a TD in a 20-13 OT win over First Coast.
